Is the military command that's responsible for

53:09.852 --> 53:12.887
essentially the conducting of the nation's military affairs

53:12.889 --> 53:14.288
in cyberspace.

53:14.790 --> 53:17.191
<i>The stated reason the United States</i>

53:17.193 --> 53:19.360
<i>decided it needed a Cyber Command</i>

53:19.362 --> 53:22.563
<i>was because of an event called Operation Buckshot Yankee.</i>

53:23.031 --> 53:24.632
Chris Inglis: <i>In the fall of 2008,</i>

53:24.634 --> 53:27.468
<i>we found some adversaries inside</i>

53:27.470 --> 53:29.070
<i>of our classified networks.</i>

53:30.005 --> 53:31.572
